OL,3,CGreenwich hospice launches appeal for
OL,4,C'once-in-a-generation' renovation
OL,6,F"But being there and having that
OL,7,Fprivacy. I could talk to him, it
OL,8,Fdidn't matter. I could say whatever I
OL,9,Fwanted to him. I could play music for
OL,10,Fhim because music was very important
OL,11,Fto him.
OL,13,F"(It was) just so important to have
OL,14,Fthat private space where I could say a
OL,15,Freally proper goodbye without having
OL,16,Fto worry."
OL,18,FThe hospice says the new rooms will
OL,19,Fbring patients and families closer to
OL,20,Fnature, offering beds by the window
OL,21,Fand direct access to gardens.
